{
  "uuid": "pGze",
  "titre": "Décomposition en éléments simples",
  "theme": "fractions rationnelles",
  "auteur": "",
  "date": "",
  "organisation": "AMSCC",
  "contenu": [
    {
      "type": "question",
      "value": "<p>Calculer la division euclidienne de <span class=\"math inline\">\\(X^5+1\\)</span> par <span class=\"math inline\">\\(X^4-2 X^3+X^2\\)</span>.</p>\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": "<p><span class=\"math display\">\\[X^5+1=(X+2) \\cdot\\left(X^4-2 X^3+X^2\\right)+3 X^3-2 X^2+1\\]</span></p>\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "question",
      "value": "<p>Factoriser dans <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\mathbb{R}[X]\\)</span> le polynôme <span class=\"math inline\">\\(X^4-2 X^3+X^2\\)</span>.</p>\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": "<p><span class=\"math display\">\\[X^4-2 X^3+X^2=X^2 \\cdot\\left(X^2-2 X+1\\right)=X^2 \\cdot(X-1)^2\\]</span></p>\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "question",
      "value": "<p>On note <span class=\"math inline\">\\(F(X)=\\frac{X^5+1}{X^4-2 X^3+X^2}\\)</span>. Donner la forme de la décomposition en éléments simples de <span class=\"math inline\">\\(F(X)\\)</span> dans <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\mathbb{R}(X)\\)</span>.</p>\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": "<p><span class=\"math display\">\\[F(X)=\\frac{X^5+1}{X^4-2 X^3+X^2}=\\frac{X^5+1}{X^2 \\cdot(X-1)^2}=X+2+\\frac{A}{X}+\\frac{B}{X^2}+\\frac{C}{(X-1)}+\\frac{D}{(X-1)^2}\\]</span></p>\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "question",
      "value": "<p>Calculer <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\lim\\limits_{X \\rightarrow 0}\\left(X^2 \\cdot F(X)\\right)\\)</span></p>\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": "<p><span class=\"math display\">\\[\\begin{aligned}\n    \\lim _{X \\rightarrow 0}\\left(X^2 \\cdot F(X)\\right) &amp; =\\lim _{X \\rightarrow 0} \\frac{X^2 \\cdot\\left(X^5+1\\right)}{X^2 \\cdot(X-1)^2}=1 \\\\\n    &amp; =\\lim _{X \\rightarrow 0} X^2 \\cdot\\left[X+2+\\frac{A}{X}+\\frac{B}{X^2}+\\frac{C}{(X-1)}+\\frac{D}{(X-1)^2}\\right]=B\n\\end{aligned}\\]</span></p>\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "question",
      "value": "<p>Calculer <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\lim\\limits_{X \\rightarrow 1}\\left((X-1)^2 \\cdot F(X)\\right)\\)</span>.</p>\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": "<p><span class=\"math display\">\\[\\begin{aligned}\n    \\lim _{X \\rightarrow 1}\\left((X-1)^2 \\cdot F(X)\\right) &amp; =\\lim _{X \\rightarrow 1} \\frac{(X A)^2 \\cdot\\left(X^5+1\\right)}{X^2 \\cdot(X-1)^2}=2 \\\\\n    &amp; =\\lim _{X \\rightarrow 1}(X-1)^2 \\cdot\\left[X+2+\\frac{A}{X}+\\frac{B}{X^2}+\\frac{C}{(X-1)}+\\frac{D}{(X-1)^2}\\right]=D\n\\end{aligned}\\]</span></p>\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "question",
      "value": "<p>Calculer <span class=\"math inline\">\\(F(-1)\\)</span> et <span class=\"math inline\">\\(F(2)\\)</span> de deux façons différentes.</p>\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": "<p><span class=\"math display\">\\[\\begin{aligned}\n    &amp; F(-1)=\\frac{(-1)^5+1}{(-1)^2 \\cdot(-1-1)^2}=0 \\\\\n    &amp;=-1+2+\\frac{A}{-1}+\\frac{1}{(-1)^2}+\\frac{C}{(-1-1)}+\\frac{2}{(-1-1)^2}=2-A-\\frac{C}{2}+\\frac{1}{2} \\\\\n    &amp; \\Rightarrow 2 A+C=5 \\\\\n    &amp; F(2)=\\frac{(2)^5+1}{(2)^2 \\cdot(2-1)^2}=\\frac{33}{4} \\\\\n    &amp;=2+2+\\frac{A}{2}+\\frac{1}{(2)^2}+\\frac{C}{(2-1)}+\\frac{2}{(2-1)^2}=4+\\frac{A}{2}+\\frac{1}{4}+C+2 \\\\\n    &amp; \\Rightarrow A+2 C=4 \\\\\n    &amp;\\left\\{\\begin{array} { l } \n        { 2 A + C = 5 } \\\\\n        { A + 2 C = 4 }\n    \\end{array} \\Leftrightarrow \\left\\{\\begin{array}{l}\n        A=2 \\\\\n        C=1\n    \\end{array}\\right.\\right.\n\\end{aligned}\\]</span></p>\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "question",
      "value": "<p>En déduire la décomposition en éléments simples de <span class=\"math inline\">\\(F(X)\\)</span> dans <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\mathbb{R}(X)\\)</span>.</p>\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": "<p><span class=\"math display\">\\[F(X)=\\frac{X^5+1}{X^4-2 X^3+X^2}=\\frac{X^5+1}{X^2 \\cdot(X-1)^2}=X+2+\\frac{2}{X}+\\frac{1}{X^2}+\\frac{1}{(X-1)}+\\frac{2}{(X-1)^2} .\\]</span></p>\n"
    }
  ]
}